to run a Mastodon server

753
00:31:29,990 --> 00:31:31,160
is open source.

754
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:33,410
So there is no location where
it's just sitting there,

755
00:31:33,410 --> 00:31:35,280
is the main source of the code.

756
00:31:35,280 --> 00:31:37,370
The entirety of
Mastodon can't go down

757
00:31:37,370 --> 00:31:39,660
without the entirety of
the internet going down.

758
00:31:39,660 --> 00:31:42,540
And that adds, again,
some redundancy,

759
00:31:42,540 --> 00:31:44,850
some reliability,
but also again,

760
00:31:44,850 --> 00:31:50,660
allows for a lot of new
ideas and new way of sharing

761
00:31:50,660 --> 00:31:52,970
information to exist.

762
00:31:52,970 --> 00:31:54,470
Think about, again,
maybe there's

763
00:31:54,470 --> 00:31:57,590
